cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST, cs.IT. 

The paper proposes a fixed parameter tractable algorithm for the problem of learning mixtures of linear regressions, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The algorithm achieves global convergence and has nearly optimal sample and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves statistical analysis and information theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
